Ibs. (the approximate reported yield in Turkey), then the area
required to produce 100,000 and 120,000 lbs. of opium is
approximately 19.4 square miles and 23.2 square miles,
respectively. (If 1 acre yields 8.07 lbs., then 12,391.5 acres
will yield 100,000 lbs. This acreage is approximately 19.4 square
miles.) On the other hand, if the true Turkish yield, as
suspected, is approximately 14 Ibs. per acre, then the area
required to produce 100,000 and 120,000 lbs. is approximately
11.2 and 13.4 square miles, respectively.</font> </p>

